      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CARISSA'S BABY (6) goes very well at this journey here having never missed the frame including two wins and two placings. Missed the frame latest (19.79) when fifth over 340m at Hobart in a Grade 5. Looks well placed and should feature. REMEMBER TOMMY (1) failed to feature last start at this track, but prior to that won by 2 lengths at this track (16.10) beating Peterina in a Free For All on February 9. Unbeaten from this box in three starts. Deserves plenty of respect. MAGIC BOOM (2) produced a modest effort most recently when sixth at this track over 278m behind Save Tonight (16.66) in a Grade 4. Has ability and can atone. DON'T SLIP MICK (3) shapes well for this after a slick 15.85 win last time. Looks an each way chance.",
